13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3218.7-2 of Title 70, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 Within The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education, no
18 resident tuition or nonresident tuition shall be charged to the
19 spouse or children of a Gold Star recipient who was killed in the
20 line of duty in any branch of the United States Armed Forces,
21 provided that either:
22 1. The Gold Star recipient was a legal resident of the State of
23 Oklahoma at the time of death; or
24
Req. No. 16954 Page 1

1 2. The spouse or child maintains residency in the State of
2 Oklahoma during enrollment.
3 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 3218.7-1, as
4 amended by Section 2, Chapter 382, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
5 Section 3218.7-1), is amended to read as follows:
6 Section 3218.7-1. A. Within The Oklahoma State System of
7 Higher Education, no fees nor room and board shall be charged to:
8 1. Children of Oklahoma peace officers as defined by Section
9 648 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes who have given their lives
10 in the line of duty;
11 2. Children of Oklahoma firefighters who have given their lives
12 in the line of duty;
13 3. Children of commissioned members of the Oklahoma Law
14 Enforcement Retirement System, who have given their lives in the
15 line of duty; and
16 4. Children of Oklahoma emergency medical technicians who have
17 given their lives in the line of duty; and
18 5. The spouse or children of a Gold Star recipient who was
19 killed in the line of duty in any branch of the United States Armed
20 Forces, provided that either:
21 a. the Gold Star recipient was a legal resident of the
22 State of Oklahoma at the time of death, or
23 b. the spouse or child maintains residency in the State
24 of Oklahoma during enrollment.
Req. No. 16954 Page 2

1 B. Such waiver of fees and room and board shall be limited to a
2 period of five (5) years.
3 C. Such waiver of fees and room and board shall be a service
4 benefit of a commissioned member of the Oklahoma Law Enforcement
5 Retirement System.
6 D. For purposes of this section:
7 1. "Firefighter" means a volunteer firefighter or a permanent
8 salaried professional member of any fire department within the State
9 of Oklahoma; and
10 2. "Emergency medical technician" means a person volunteering
11 or employed as an emergency medical technician and who is licensed
12 as an emergency medical technician pursuant to Section 1-2505 of
13 Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
14 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 14-134, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 14-134. A. Within the system of career technology
17 districts, no resident tuition or nonresident tuition shall be
18 charged to the:
19 1. Children of Oklahoma peace officers as defined by Section
20 648 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes who have given their lives
21 in the line of duty;
22 2. Children of Oklahoma firefighters who have given their lives
23 in the line of duty;
24
Req. No. 16954 Page 3

1 3. Children of members of the Oklahoma Law Enforcement
2 Retirement System who have given their lives in the line of duty or
3 whose disability is by means of personal and traumatic injury of a
4 catastrophic nature, as defined by Section 2-300 of Title 47 of the
5 Oklahoma Statutes, and occurred in the line of duty; and
6 4. Children of Oklahoma emergency medical technicians who have
7 given their lives in the line of duty; and
8 5. The spouse or children of a Gold Star recipient who was
9 killed in the line of duty in any branch of the United States Armed
10 Forces, provided that either:
11 a. the Gold Star recipient was a legal resident of the
12 State of Oklahoma at the time of death, or
13 b. the spouse or child maintains residency in the State
14 of Oklahoma during enrollment.
15 B. Such waiver of resident tuition and nonresident tuition
16 shall be limited to a period of five (5) years.
17 C. Such waiver of resident tuition or nonresident tuition to
18 the children of deceased peace officers and to the children of
19 deceased firefighters as provided for in this section shall be a
20 service benefit of each Oklahoma peace officer and Oklahoma
21 firefighter.
22 D. For purposes of this section:
